<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>Charles Schwab (SCHW)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of The Charles Schwab Corporation.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated {new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0]} &middot; Data: FY{latestYear || 'Latest'}</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentPrice.toFixed(2)} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{revenueCurrent ? '$' + (revenueCurrent / 1000).toFixed(1) + 'B' : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">FY{latestYear || 'Latest'} Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{fcfCurrent ? '$' + (fcfCurrent / 1000).toFixed(1) + 'B' : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{epsCurrent ? '$' + epsCurrent.toFixed(2) : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{operatingMarginCurrent ? operatingMarginCurrent.toFixed(1) + '%' : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{netCash ? '$' + (netCash / 1000).toFixed(1) + 'B' : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model to estimate Charles Schwab's intrinsic value based on future cash flows.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>We begin with the latest reported Free Cash Flow. For financial institutions like Schwab, cash flows can fluctuate wildly due to client cash sorting and balance sheet changes. We use <strong>{fcfCurrent ? '$' + fcfCurrent.toLocaleString() + ' million' : 'N/A'}</strong> from FY{latestYear || 'Latest'} as our base.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We grow FCF at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}% per year</strong> for 5 years. This assumes a stabilization of client deposits, net interest margin expansion post-Fed rate hikes, and continued steady asset gathering in their wealth management business.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}% forever</strong>. This uses the Gordon Growth Model: Terminal Value = FCF₆ &divide; (discount rate &minus; terminal growth rate). It represents Schwab's mature growth rate as a staple financial services platform.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>We discount all future cash flows at <strong>{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</strong>. With the 10Y Treasury at 4.18%, we add a suitable equity risk premium, taking into account the duration risk and interest rate sensitivity inherent in Schwab's balance sheet.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
      <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash ({netCash ? '$' + netCash.toLocaleString() + 'M' : 'N/A'}) = Equity Value. We divide by shares outstanding ({sharesOutstanding ? sharesOutstanding.toLocaleString() + 'M' : 'N/A'}) to get intrinsic value per share.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Schwab faced "cash sorting" headwinds as interest rates rose, hurting Net Interest Revenue. We model 8% growth assuming these headwinds subside and the underlying asset management and trading businesses resume their steady, compounding growth trajectory.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        10Y Treasury is 4.18%. Financials carry higher inherent balance sheet risk (as seen in the 2023 regional banking crisis, which also pressured Schwab's stock). A 9.5% discount rate demands a healthy premium to hold their equity.
      </div>
    </div>
